    <h2><a href="articles/setting-up-l-vr-in-vscode">Setting up LÖVR in vscode</a></h2>
    <div class="variables">
    <div class="date">@date=2025-04-27</div>
    <div class="tags">@tags=<a href="tags/lovr">lovr</a>, <a href="tags/coding">coding</a>, <a href="tags/vscode">vscode</a></div>
    </div>
    <article>
        <p>This was taken down, and I found it in the web archive here:</p>
<p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20230209043024/https://gist.github.com/ussaohelcim/9eca6eaa903eefff07b4f3e2019de915">https://web.archive.org/web/20230209043024/https://gist.github.com/ussaohelcim/9eca6eaa903eefff07b4f3e2019de915</a></p>
<h3>Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>vscode</li>
<li>Lua Language Server coded by Lua by sumneko<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/sumneko/lua-language-server">https://github.com/sumneko/lua-language-server</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>lovr api docs<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/bjornbytes/lovr-docs/tree/master/api">https://github.com/bjornbytes/lovr-docs/tree/master/api</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h3>How to</h3>
<ul>
<li>install <code>lua language server</code> extension in your vscode</li>
<li>download <code>lovr api docs</code> somewhere<ul>
<li>git clone <a href="https://github.com/bjornbytes/lovr-docs.git">https://github.com/bjornbytes/lovr-docs.git</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>open <code>lua language server</code> extension settings</li>
<li>search for <code>Lua › Workspace: Library</code></li>
<li>press add item</li>
<li>insert the docs api full path 
<img data-src="images/Pasted image 20250429114249.png" alt="Pasted image 20250429114249.png" style="max-width: 100%;" /></li>
<li>you are ready to go</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>Other things I found useful</h3>
<p><a href="https://github.com/mcclure/lodr">https://github.com/mcclure/lodr</a></p>

